===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A person who or animal that does not eat any [[animal]] [[flesh]].<!--Incorrect: the following defines a vegan, which is not the same thing: "one who consumes only [[vegetable]] and [[inorganic]] matter (e.g., water); [[vegan]]; [[herbivore]]."-->
# A person whose diet excludes [[animal]] [[flesh]], but may include food that can be produced from a living animal without causing death or undue suffering (such as eggs, honey, and [[dairy product]]s); [[lacto-ovo-vegetarian]].
#* '''''Vegetarian''' – that’s an old Indian word for 'lousy hunter.' '' &mdash; Andy Rooney
# A person whose diet excludes flesh from land-based or airborne [[vertebrate]]s, but does include other forms of animal products (e.g., fish or eggs); a [[pescatarian]].
<!--This is hardly a vegetarian, just a man of common sense; indeed, it is not a vegetarian as meat-eating contradicts the term:
# A person whose diet excludes animal products ([[meat]], [[dairy]], etc.) produced under cruel circumstances.  -->

====Synonyms====
*(''person or animal who does not eat any animal products''): [[herbivore]] (''the usual term used for an animal'')
*(''person who does not eat animal flesh but eats other animal products''): [[lacto-ovo-vegeterian]], [[ovo-lacto-vegetarian]], [[ovolactovegetarian]]
*(''person who does not eat meat but does eat fish''): [[pescatarian]]

====Antonyms====
*(''person who or animal that does not eat any animal products''): [[carnivore]] (''animal eating meat alone; person whose diet includes meat''), [[omnivore]] (''animal eating meat and vegetable matter'')

